description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Registered Nurse with experience working inanNHS hospital? Why not join Whittington Health Trust? We are ranked as ‘Outstanding’ for caring by the Care Quality Commission. If you are looking for flexible work that can fit around your other commitments this could be just what you are looking for!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Variety of Early, Late, Long Days &amp; Night Shifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good Support from a central Clinical lead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Priority of shifts over an agency worker, accommodating your availability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A dedicated recruitment team to ensure you can work as quickly as possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A bookings team to ensure you work when and wherever you want to&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required Skills:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1stlevel registered nurse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A least 6 months acute NHS experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Posses a diverse range of clinical skills and the ability to work unsupervised&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please apply today by completing the application box below.&lt;/p&gt;
